<statement>
<p>Below, one description, one graph, and one equation are equivalent.  Choose the proper set.</p>
<p><ul label="circle"><li><p>You start with 1 Xbox games and each month you buy 4 new games.</p></li> 
<li><p>You start with 2 Xbox games and each month you buy 2 new games.</p></li> 
</ul></p>
<p><ul label="circle"><li><figure><image source="https://myopenmaths3.s3.amazonaws.com/gimgs/ca21e481326ef400c84685f253621274.png" /></figure></li> 
<li><figure><image source="https://myopenmaths3.s3.amazonaws.com/gimgs/bdb48f05c21ac5e8dfd05abc7f6345f5.png" /></figure></li> 
</ul></p>
<p><ul label="circle"><li><p><m>\displaystyle{y}={4}{x}+{1}</m></p></li> 
<li><p><m>\displaystyle{y}={2}{x}+{2}</m></p></li> 
</ul></p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><p>You start with 1 Xbox games and each month you buy 4 new games.</p></li><li><figure><image source="https://myopenmaths3.s3.amazonaws.com/gimgs/ca21e481326ef400c84685f253621274.png" /></figure></li><li><p><m>\displaystyle{y}={4}{x}+{1}</m></p></li></ul></p>
</solution>
